<topic id='business_definition_accident_and_emergency_attendance_conclusion_date.description'>
  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>NHS Business Definition: Accident and Emergency Attendance Conclusion Date - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
  <div>
      <p>
An 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_accident_and_emergency_attendance_conclusion_date">Accident and Emergency Attendance Conclusion Date</xref>
 is an 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_activity_date_time">ACTIVITY DATE TIME</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
An 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_accident_and_emergency_attendance_conclusion_date">Accident and Emergency Attendance Conclusion Date</xref>
 is the date:        </p>
      <ul>
         <li>
            <div>
               <p>
that a 
                                <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>'s 
                                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_accident_and_emergency_attendance">Accident and Emergency Attendance</xref>
 concludes or                    </p>
            </div>
         </li>
         <li>
            <div>
               <p>
when treatment in the 
                                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_accident_and_emergency_department">Accident and Emergency Department</xref>
 is completed (whichever is the later).                    </p>
            </div>
         </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
For those 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENTS</xref>
 admitted into hospital, the 
              <xref outputclass="element"
               keyref="element_accident_and_emergency_attendance_conclusion_date">ACCIDENT AND EMERGENCY ATTENDANCE CONCLUSION DATE</xref>
 is recorded as the date when the 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_decision_to_admit">DECISION TO ADMIT</xref>
 was made.        </p>
  </div>
</body>
